cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of channel assignment in cognitive radio networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper applies two economic models, matching markets and competitive markets, to solve the problem, which involves game theory and mechanism design (cs.GT). The paper also considers the performance of the algorithms in terms of achievable rate, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The coordination algorithms proposed in the paper involve distributed decision-making and adaptation to network dynamics, which are topics in control and systems theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes numerical simulations to illustrate the performance of the proposed solutions, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
